Itâ€™s Holy Week, the most impactful and famous week in human history. Jerusalem is a powder keg with all of Jesusâ€™ followers, enemies, and over a million Passover pilgrims packed into one small place. He shows sides of Himself weâ€™ve never seen till nowâ€”turning over tables, literally cracking the whip, and weeping with heartbreak but also love. He also confuses His followers at every turn...and to what end?

The takeaway for you from this season: Can you believe and follow even when you don't understand?

Yes, itâ€™s sad and heartbreaking because weâ€™re getting closer to the cross, but weâ€™re also going to get to see some of the most iconic and deeply moving moments from Scripture. The triumphal entry, the turning of the tables, the betrayal by Judas, and the Last Supper...all set against the biggest backdrop and sets we've ever used with a new widescreen format that demands to be seen on the big screen. But of course, we continue our obsession to humanize and authenticate everyone involved.

The table is set. I can't wait for you to see this in theaters.

Dallas Jenkins
Creator, The Chosen

Weâ€™ve just hit 10 million subscribers on YouTube, and weâ€™re celebrating with the one youâ€™ve all been waiting forâ€¦ Bugatti vs Koenigsegg Carwow drag race! 

Mat and the team have flown out to Dubai to get their hands on these awesome hypercars, and theyâ€™re about to go head-to-head as they race over the quarter-mile for the chequered flag. But which will come out on top? Letâ€™s take a closer look at the stats. 

Starting with the Bugatti, itâ€™s the Chiron Super Sport, which comes with an 8-litre quad-turbo W16 that produces 1600hp and 1600Nm of torque. This power is sent to all four wheels via a 7-speed dual-clutch automatic gearbox, and the car weighs 1,995kg. Following several interior & exterior modifications, the car we have here is valued at Â£5,000,000.

Alongside it, we have the Koenigsegg Jesko Attack. This is powered by a 5-litre twin-turbo V8, and this creates 1280hp and 1000Nm. This power is sent to the rear wheels only via a 9-speed multi-clutch gearbox, and it weighs a whole lot less than the Bugatti, tipping the scales at just 1,420kg! But just like the Chiron Super Sport, it has a price tag of Â£5,000,000. 

So the Bugatti is well up on power, but it weighs half a tonne more than the Koenigsegg! Could the weight difference prove decisive? Thereâ€™s only one way to find out for sureâ€¦ LETâ€™S RACE!

jNnsTNZR2bU.title: Leon Thomas: Tiny Desk Concert
jNnsTNZR2bU.description:
Bobby Carter | February 20, 2025
On the morning of Leon Thomas' Tiny Desk concert, many NPR staffers assumed the show was postponed due to a snowstorm in the D.C. area. Not only did he proactively schedule his coast-to-coast flight but he was also 30 minutes early to the office. With his sophomore album, MUTT, Thomas has planted his flag as the most exciting artist in R&B music today. The Tiny Desk had to happen now; nothing would get in the way of divine timing.

Thomas was destined to be an entertainer â€” he's been doing it for most of his life. His parents were both musicians and introduced him to their world early on. As an actor, he appeared in multiple Broadway plays before becoming a staple on the Nickelodeon network. Under the tutelage of Babyface, he earned his chops as a writer and producer, eventually penning and producing big hits in R&B and hip-hop.

He opens this set with three songs from MUTT and closes with two from 2023's Electric Dusk, including "Breaking Point," which he dedicates to his recently deceased grandfather, the opera singer John Anthony: "This is one of his favorite songs."
